🔥 Production Scenario

Problem: You cannot SSH into a production server.

Investigation

Check if the SSH service is running:

sudo systemctl status ssh

Verify port 22 is listening:

ss -tuln | grep :22

Check firewall rules:

sudo ufw status

Review SSH logs:

Ubuntu:

sudo journalctl -u ssh

or

sudo tail -f /var/log/auth.log

Verify the user's .ssh directory permissions:

chmod 700 ~/.ssh
chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

Test with verbose output:

ssh -vvv username@server-ip
